Package: hanziR
Title: Terminal-Based Hanzi Learning Card Manager
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Lee", "Durbin", , "hello@leedurbin.co.nz", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A minimal R package providing a console app for managing 
    Chinese character (Hanzi) learning cards with accessible tone cues 
    and multiple export formats. Features include YAML-based storage,
    full-text search, filtering, and export to Markdown, CSV, and Anki formats.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/lddurbin/hanziR
BugReports: https://github.com/lddurbin/hanziR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    yaml,
    cli,
    glue,
    tibble,
    dplyr,
    purrr,
    stringr,
    readr,
    rlang
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
